name: Robot Rock / Oh Yeah
wikiSummary: "Robot Rock / Oh Yeah" is the first track of thirteen on Daft Punk's, 'Alive 2007' album.  The album is a recording from multiple locations of their Alive 2007 world tour which debuted out of Bercy.  The track is a mash-up of their tracks, "Robot Rock" and "Oh Yeah" with stunning visuals and seamless effects flowing from their pyramid, this is just another masterpiece by the masters of French Electro.
wikiText:
"Robot Rock / Oh Yeah" is the first track of thirteen on Daft Punk's, 'Alive 2007' album.
 
 The album is a recording from multiple locations of their Alive 2007 world tour which debuted out of Bercy.
 
 The track is a mash-up of their tracks, "Robot Rock" and "Oh Yeah" with stunning visuals and seamless effects flowing from their pyramid, this is just another masterpiece by the masters of French Electro.
